Four people were reportedly killed on Wednesday morning when a truck driver lost control and ran the vehicle into a taxi and three commercial motorcycles in Ibadan, the Oyo State capital. The incident happened at the Aleshinloye Roundabout. While three people died inside the taxi, a commercial motorcyclist died on the spot. Response of the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) Mr Olugbenga Fadeyi in the state was being expected at press time. In Ogun State, a speeding truck also ran into a car along Papa-Ilaro Road, crushing the three occupants to death, including the driver. Spokesman of the state Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps (TRACE), Babatunde Akinbiyi, confirmed the incident.